<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-02T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="68" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89Czechoslovakia/90:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-02T13:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 2,
                                            1925—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:55
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>12. Your instruction number 252, April 4th. Presented note
                                    today.<note n="9" xml:id="d68fn9">Note dated April 30.</note>
                                Dr. Beneš denies any intention of discriminating against the United
                                States by arranging payment of so-called Nansen relief bonds and
                                believes such impression is based on misunderstanding. Will write me
                                in explanation.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Einstein</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>